examples.en: There's no way out! We're trapped!
He was trapped in a difficult situation.
She felt trapped in an empty marriage.
I was trapped into signing a confession.
They were trapped after the lifts went out of action.
Dozens of people were trapped in the rubble when the building collapsed.
Julia felt trapped in her role of wife and mother.
The toxic fumes imperiled the lives of the trapped miners.
The police trapped the terrorists at a roadblock.
In The Odyssey, Ulysses is trapped between the six-headed monster Scylla and Charybdis, a deadly whirlpool that threatens to suck in his ship.
One regiment was trapped behind enemy lines.
